TLDR;
To those affected:
-Be patient 
-Open Sea knows they are in the wrong
-Open Sea has the funds to make this right
-Open Sea will make it right
-The ball is in their hand to make things right or they will suffer in the end  
Also know that the community is here for you.
(8/8)

Open Sea should be held accountable for this & to the credit of Open Sea, they have seemed to claim responsibility for these sales by refunding those affected. It is somewhat a lengthy process to get those refunded & may take a thorough investigation into each sale to verify 7/8

This is something that has happened because of their website and it not including the proper tools to allow users to not get exploited like this. There are some computer jerks that have the back end data in open sea to get these NFTs for pennies on the dollar. 6/8

In the past, people have lost their NFTs due to their own negligence including clicking links, giving out seed phrases, etc. These old scenarios had nothing to do with Open Sea and they were not and should not have been held accountable. However, this is different. 5/8

Now why is this important?
In the last week there have been countless NFTs exploited that have sold well below their current values caused from Open Sea's back end data that was not visible to their users. 4/8
To summarize that total: they have sent 12,500 to coinbase in the last 3 weeks alone and are sitting on 44,000 eth + other tokens. 3/8

Just in the last 21 days they have sent a total of 12,500 eth to a coinbase wallet (i would assume to swap to fiat).
